To run spaghettikart you have to provide game assets, a ROM in z64 format.

There are some links that could help in this regard.
https://github.com/HarbourMasters/SpaghettiKart
https://github.com/sanni/cartreader

spaghettikart opens a dialog to let you choose the ROM in z64 format.
Depending on your desktop environment, install one of the dialog helper:

doas pkg_add zenity # dialogs for GNOME
doas pkg_add kdialog # KDE dialog boxes from shell scripts

Otherwise, run the following command with your ROM, replace baserom.z64
 with the actual ROM path on your system.

${LOCALBASE}/share/spaghettikart/torch o2r \
	-s ${LOCALBASE}/share/spaghettikart -d ~/.local/share/spaghettify \
	-a ${LOCALBASE}/share/spaghettikart/meta/mods.toml \
	baserom.z64

For a better UI experience you may use a texture pack:
https://evilgames.eu/texture-packs.htm

Pre-made .o2r are directly compatible with shipwrightsoh and are built from:
https://github.com/GhostlyDark/MK64-Reloaded-SK

For example, to use HD pack (alternatively, can also use GitHub release assets):
cd ~/.local/share/spaghettify/mods/
ftp https://evilgames.eu/files/texture-packs/mk64-reloaded-v2025.12.20-sk-hd.o2r
